    <stitle>CE 200, CE 300 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - REMOVE - Splash Panels</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Splash Panels</title>
        <para>The splash panels (
            <hotlnk document="s09009_5.xml" xrefid="f0900904">Figure 4 and 5</hotlnk>) on the CE Series bus chassis
            minimize splash and mud, protecting vital engine systems from corrosion and malfunction.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tilt the hood assembly forward and locate the splash panel mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900925">Figure 35, Item 2</hotlnk>) at the lower section of the splash panel. Loosen
                and remove the splash panel mounting bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the upper splash panel mounting bolts (also Item 2). Loosen and remove the mounting
                bolts attaching the splash panel to the upper section of the hood assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the splash panel.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow the same procedure for the opposite side splash panel assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0900925" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900925.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 35. Splash Panel Removal (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HOOD STOP CABLE ATTACHMENT BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SPLASH PANEL MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SPLASH PANEL</callout1>
                <callout1>4. GRILLE INSERT</callout1>
                <callout1>5. HINGE CROSS BAR</callout1>
                <callout1>6. RADIATOR TOP FRAME ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
